نائِب (نُوّاب) || nāʾib (nuwwāb)%deputy% 19 % Derived from the active participle of نَابَ‎ (nāba, “to represent, to act as a deputy”), from the root ن و ب‎ (n-w-b). Compare نَابَ "to replace, to substitute; to act on behalf of, to represent; to nod assent to, to agree with, to turn towards"
الاِقْتِصاد%the economy% 19 % Verbal noun of اِقْتَصَدَ‎ (iqtaṣada), from the root ق ص د‎ (q-ṣ-d).  "Related to objectives, projects". Compare قَصَدَ "to mean, to intend"
