صَلَّح / يُصَلِّح%to mend/fix% 19 % From the root ص ل ح‎ (ṣ-l-ḥ) "forms words relating to righteousness or correcting". Different root from Unit 16 صَحا "to wake up" (ص ح و, related to purity and clearing), Unit 18 الصِحَّة "health" (ص ح ح, "relating to health and truth").
نَظَّف / يُنَظِّف%to clean% 19* % From the root ن ظ ف‎ (n-ẓ-f). Form I is نَظُفَ • (naẓufa) I, non-past يَنْظُفُ‎ (yanẓufu), "to be clean".
